%pyspark
# Getting different types of skills from csv files
tech_skill_data = sqlContext.read.load('/zeppelin/data/techskill.csv', format='com.databricks.spark.csv', header='true', inferSchema='true')
non_tech_skill_data = sqlContext.read.load('/zeppelin/data/nontechnicalskills.csv', format='com.databricks.spark.csv', header='true', inferSchema='true')
legal_skill_data = sqlContext.read.load('/zeppelin/data/legal.csv', format='com.databricks.spark.csv', header='true', inferSchema='true')

# Converting skills to list form
tech_list = tech_skill_data.columns
non_tech_list = non_tech_skill_data.columns
legal_list = legal_skill_data.columns

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import Row
from pyspark.sql.functions import row_number,lit,concat_ws
from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from pyspark.sql.types import StructType, StructField, StringType, DoubleType

# Replacing list with skills 
lower_list = data.select('lower').collect()
def skillList(your_list,lower_list_temp):
    count =0
    for i in lower_list_temp:
        techskills = []
        for j in your_list:
            if " "+str(j)+" " in str(i):
                techskills.append(j)
            elif " "+str(j)+"," in str(i):
                techskills.append(j)
            elif " "+str(j)+"." in str(i):
                techskills.append(j)
        lower_list_temp[count] = techskills
        count = count+1
    return lower_list_temp
    
# Getting tech skills 
tech_skill_list = skillList(tech_list,lower_list)
# tech skill data frame
rdd1 = sc.parallelize(tech_skill_list)
row_rdd = rdd1.map(lambda x: Row(x))
df2=sqlContext.createDataFrame(row_rdd,['techskills'])
# adding ID column to new dataframe
w = Window().orderBy(lit('techskills'))
df2 = df2.withColumn("ID", row_number().over(w))
df2= df2.withColumn('techskills', concat_ws(',', 'techskills'))

%pyspark
# Getting non tech skills
non_tech_skill_list = skillList(non_tech_list,data.select('lower').collect())
# schema1 = StructType([StructField("nontechskills", StringType(), True)])
# non tech skill data frame
rdd2 = sc.parallelize(non_tech_skill_list)
row_rdd2 = rdd2.map(lambda x: Row(x))
df3=sqlContext.createDataFrame(row_rdd2,["nontechskills"])
# adding ID column to new dataframe
w = Window().orderBy(lit('nontechskills'))
df3 = df3.withColumn("ID", row_number().over(w))
df3= df3.withColumn('nontechskills', concat_ws(',', 'nontechskills'))
# df3.show()

%pyspark
# Getting Legal Skills
legal_skill_list = skillList(legal_list,data.select('lower').collect())
# schema2 = StructType([StructField("legalskills", StringType(), True)])
# legal skill data frame
rdd3 = sc.parallelize(legal_skill_list)
row_rdd3 = rdd3.map(lambda x: Row(x))
df4=sqlContext.createDataFrame(row_rdd3,["legalskills"])
# adding ID column to new dataframe
w = Window().orderBy(lit('legalskills'))
df4 = df4.withColumn("ID", row_number().over(w))
df4= df4.withColumn('legalskills', concat_ws(',', 'legalskills'))

%pyspark
# Merging two data frames to one
new_df = data.join(df2, on=['ID'], how='inner')
new_df = new_df.join(df3, on=['ID'], how='inner')
new_df = new_df.join(df4, on=['ID'], how='inner')
# new_df = new_df.withColumn('techskills1', regexp_extract(data['techskills'],r'/[\[\]']+/g', 1))
new_df.show()

job_data1 = job_data1.join(df5, on=['ID'], how='inner')

%pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud
# BAR CHART 1

# Getting job descriptions with coding requerement
tech_dict = {'c':0,'c++':0,'java':0,'python':0,'javascript':0,'sql':0,'matlab':0,'jquery':0,'spark':0}
for key in tech_dict:
    tech_dict[key]=job_data1.where(col('techskills').like("%"+key+"%")).count()

# Plotting graph for most required language in Job Descriptions 
# plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)

plt.bar(range(len(tech_dict)), list(tech_dict.values()), align='center')
plt.xticks(rotation=20)
plt.xticks(range(len(tech_dict)), list(tech_dict.keys()))
plt.title("Most Required Language in the Job Descriptions")
plt.xlabel('tech skills')
plt.ylabel('Occurences in Job Descriptions')
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

# plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
wc = WordCloud(background_color="white",width=1000,height=1000, max_words=10,relative_scaling=0.5,normalize_plurals=False).generate_from_frequencies(tech_dict)
plt.axis('off')
plt.imshow(wc)
plt.show()
